node.text:
Phantom of the Opera, work-in-progress.

Still suffering from BPPV. Slept most of yesterday and today. The anti-nausea meds kicked in so I didn't feel like puking my guts out every time I moved my head. 

Decided to draw for couple of hours which was a challenge. Tilting my head and body forward to draw made the vertigo and nausea worse. To be honest, I can cope with the vertigo, it's the nausea that's killing me. Been popping Meclizine Hydrochloride tablets like Tic-Tacs to keep my vomiting at bay. Seems to be working.

I've been able to pencil out this Phantom of the Opera piece this evening. It was pretty funny watching the paper sway as I drew the figures.  It felt like drawing while drunk minus the euphoria. Thank the universe for erasers. 

I will definitely not attempt any inking until I'm fully recovered from my BPPV episode. 

I shouldn't push it, but I think I'll knock out a Fight Girls page before my anti-nausea meds wears off.  Knock on wood.

@frankchoartist #frankchoartist #phantomoftheopera #phantom #lonchaney #opera #pencilsketch #music

node.text:
Fight Girls #1, Bedrock City store signing was fantastic!

The store was packed. After 3 hours of signing, they had to capped the line. 

Afterward, we had a fantastic dinner at Terry Moore’s house. Got to hang out and saw Terry’s Strangers in Paradise and Rachel Rising original art. Robyn Moore was superb host and cook. Thank you Terry, Robyn, Kelsey, Richard and crew for a delightful evening.

Houston, Hilton fitness room. 

Traveling nonstop this month. (My fourth signing in five weeks.) My sleep cycle is completely shot. Woke up at 6:10am and couldn’t fall back asleep. 

Walked/jogged 2 miles and worked out. Hopefully, I can nap before my Bedrock City Comics store signing at 1:00pm.

The good news is that I’m writing up a storm on Fight Girls. 😄
